result.execSummary:
The defendant Jeffrey Robert Hausladen was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jeffrey Robert Hausladen is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jeffrey Robert Hausladen was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "B"], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Recites agreement. Has no position on the request for expungement. Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads NO CONTEST to Ct 1 in 15CM450. DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of Ct 1 in 15CM450. On motion of the State, Crt dismisses Ct 2 in 15CM450. Sentencing arguments. Court directs Atty Christiansen to file bill within 15 days. Crt orders:

- $500 fine inclusive of costs. Bond on file to apply. Remaining bond money will remain until we receive attorney bill
